The paper discusses a new paradigm for automatic generation of training data using affinity coding, which is a machine learning technique. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also focuses on labeling image datasets, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper proposes a system called GOGGLES that uses convolutional neural nets, which is a common technique in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the quality of labels generated, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
